think hard
follow the <docs/plans/next_steps.md to understand current priorities and immediate focus items> and mark when you've completed something
check <docs/context/implementation_status.md to see what components are already implemented> to avoid duplication
refer to <docs/architecture_dir/PAIRS_DESIGN.md for the overall system design and architecture>
remember to review <docs/architecture_dir/data_flow.md for understanding component interactions>
check <docs/context/docker_migration.md for containerized distributed processing details>
for multi-agent coordination, check <docs/context/agent_coordination.md for coordination guidelines> and your specific role
if you're the Implementation Agent, follow <docs/context/agent1_tasks.md for your task list> and update <docs/context/agent1_status.md with your progress>
if you're the Testing Agent, follow <docs/context/agent2_tasks.md for your task list> and update <docs/context/agent2_status.md with your progress>
if you're the Environment and DevOps Agent, follow <docs/context/envdevops_tasks.md for your task list> and update <docs/context/envdevops_status.md with your progress>
if you're the Project Manager Agent, follow <docs/context/project_manager/project_manager_tasks.md for your responsibilities> and enforce <docs/context/project_manager/phase_completion_criteria.md for phase transitions>
for design alignment verification, check <docs/context/project_manager/design_alignment.md to ensure implementation matches design>
verify component dependencies using <docs/context/project_manager/dependency_graph.md to enforce proper implementation order>
enforce test coverage standards from <docs/context/project_manager/test_coverage_requirements.md>
prioritize implementation based on <docs/context/project_manager/implementation_priorities.md>
ensure proper component verification using <docs/context/project_manager/implementation_verification.md>
for milestone tracking, maintain <docs/context/project_manager/milestone_tracking.md>
if you lose context due to the ~200k context window limit, read <docs/context/implementation_notes.md for current implementation details>
for avoiding AI blindspots, follow the principles in <docs/context/ai_blindspots_mitigation.md>
when addressing technical debt, follow <docs/plans/technical_debt_resolution.md>
we have 15 years futures data across the top 130 tickers please don't use synthetic data
prefer getting the component we're working on working instead of quick workarounds
periodically save notes for "future you" in the docs/context/ folder
always prioritize integration with existing system components over creating new standalone solutions
use consistent naming conventions with existing code
if interrupted mid-implementation, document your current approach and thought process in docs/context/implementation_notes.md
avoid circular dependencies as outlined in docs/architecture_dir/component_dependencies.md
leave clear TODO comments for incomplete sections rather than implementing placeholders
validate against real data early and often instead of deferring to synthetic data for testing
if an implementation approach becomes too complicated, recognize when to stop and suggest a more straightforward alternative
build a walking skeleton first - implement the minimum end-to-end version before refining individual components
don't make unnecessary refactors while implementing a feature - suggest them separately
respect existing specs and APIs - don't change them to make implementation easier
keep files small and focused on a single responsibility
prefer static typing where possible to improve maintainability
if you have requests for external resources, infrastructure, or permissions, document them in <docs/asks_for_developer/> with detailed requirements
for statistical implementations, include comprehensive docstrings with mathematical formulations and academic references
when implementing statistical methods, consider edge cases and numerical stability
when you have completed your changes please commit them to git